cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual place recognition and proposes a new network architecture for the task.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as visual place recognition is an important task in robotics, especially for autonomous navigation.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the proposed network architecture is trained in an end-to-end manner and uses attention blocks, which are common in machine learning.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with a task that requires intelligence and proposes a new network architecture that improves the state-of-the-art.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with image retrieval and proposes a new network architecture that can be applied to standard image retrieval datasets.
